## UNIT CONVERSION — READ THIS FIRST

Treasury tables show values "in thousands" or "in millions" (check table title). Questions may ask for DIFFERENT units.
- "nominal dollars" or "in dollars" = raw dollars. MULTIPLY by 1000 if table is "in thousands", by 1000000 if "in millions".
- "in millions" and table is also "in millions" = no conversion needed.
- "in billions" = divide millions by 1000.
- "in thousands" and table is also "in thousands" = no conversion needed.
ALWAYS check and convert units explicitly in your Python code.

Unit indicators hide in FOUR places — check ALL before extracting: (1) table title ("Table X — in millions of dollars"), (2) subtitle/header row above columns, (3) individual column headers, (4) footnotes. Missing a unit indicator is the #1 cause of wrong answers.

```python
