## Known pitfalls
- Fiscal year ≠ calendar year. Before 1976: FY ran Jul 1 – Jun 30 (FY1940 = Jul 1939 – Jun 1940). After 1976: FY runs Oct 1 – Sep 30. Transition quarter: Jul–Sep 1976.
- Row indentation = subcategory. Parent row = total of children.
- Column headers span sub-columns — always use the full dash-separated path.
- False cognates: "Receipts" (tax revenue) ≠ "Receipts" (securities). "Expenditures" ≈ "Outlays" but not always identical. "Gross debt" includes intragovernmental; "Debt held by public" excludes it.
- When extracting a time series, verify values don't suddenly jump by 1000x mid-series — you switched tables or units.
- For historical groupings (gold bloc, etc.), verify membership via web search if uncertain.
- Document versioning: specific bulletin reference → use THAT bulletin's values. No specific bulletin → prefer the LATEST bulletin covering that period. Check next 1-2 months for revised figures.
- Pre-1996 bulletins have OCR artifacts: l↔1, O↔0, missing commas, decimal↔comma confusion. If a number looks implausible, suspect OCR error and cross-reference.
- Step budget: if you haven't found data after ~10 search attempts, write your best estimate to /app/answer.txt. A partial answer beats a timeout (score = 0).

